Umuahia- As part of her effects to sensitize Abia citizens on how to contain the second wave of COVID-19 in the state, the Abia State Director, National Orientation Agency, (NOA), Dr. Mrs. Ngozi Okeckukwu has called on Abia citizens as well as those returning to the state for the festivities to celebrate with caution, stressing that there are indications that the second wave of Covid-19 pandemic has started taking its toll on Nigerians. Dr. Okechukwu made this call when she paid an unscheduled visit to the Ngwa Road Motherless Babies home, Aba, to sensitize the management of the charity home on the need to adopt all safety measures as recommended by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). She contended that it is only when the people adopt the required behavioural pattern that the effect of COVID-19 will be defeated, urging the management of home to ensure that the children are well protected from the pandemic. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! According to the NOA Director, the theme of the agency’s sensitization in this second wave of Coronavirus is: “Building a People of Peace, Working Together to Overcome Covid-19 in Abia State.” She stressed that while celebrating the Christmas and the new year, people should remember to celebrate responsibly, to stay at home, avoid large gathering, hand shake, use sanitizer always, wear face mask, while maintaining physical/social distancing of at least two meters apart. New Strain Of COVID-19: Expert Tasks Nigerians On Safety Protocol Nigeria Would Rely On Imported COVID-19 Vaccines – NAFDAC DG Her word, “This is the time to pray for our nation to overcome her numerous challenges and the recovery of all those affected by the virus”. The Abia NOA boss also used the occasion to provide Christmas palliatives to the motherless babies, tasking Nigerians on the need to assist t